1
00:01:51,250 --> 00:01:53,130
Can't breathe...!

2
00:02:14,690 --> 00:02:16,570
Damn! They got away!

3
00:02:18,030 --> 00:02:19,870
They're lucky.

4
00:02:19,870 --> 00:02:23,990
You're pretty carefree considering
you let our prey get away from us!

5
00:02:23,990 --> 00:02:28,340
Do something, Captain!
Let's go after 'em and take 'em down!

6
00:02:29,080 --> 00:02:33,290
Don't fret, Burgess.
They'll be back eventually.

7
00:02:33,290 --> 00:02:37,340
We'll run into 'em soon enough
as long as we're on the Grand Line.

8
00:02:37,340 --> 00:02:39,110
Precisely.

9
00:02:39,110 --> 00:02:45,350
Intense desires drive the cogs 
that make the world turn.

10
00:02:47,110 --> 00:02:48,850
See?!

11
00:02:48,850 --> 00:02:50,550
Give me a break!

12
00:03:10,620 --> 00:03:15,130
Damn... What happened?!
Is everyone here?!

13
00:03:17,880 --> 00:03:20,670
Hey, guys! Look outside the ship!

14
00:03:21,490 --> 00:03:22,980
What is this place?!

15
00:03:22,980 --> 00:03:24,850
It's pure white!

16
00:03:24,850 --> 00:03:25,740
Clouds?!

17
00:03:25,740 --> 00:03:28,560
We're on the clouds?!
How are we floating on them?!

18
00:03:28,560 --> 00:03:30,730
Of course we can float!
They're clouds!

19
00:03:30,730 --> 00:03:32,020
– That's not how it works!
– That's not how it works!

20
00:03:33,730 --> 00:03:35,960
Oh, no! Usopp isn't breathing!

21
00:03:35,960 --> 00:03:38,830
What?! Do something!
Give mouth-to-mouth!

22
00:03:38,830 --> 00:03:41,530
Okay! I'll give Nami mouth-to-mouth!

23
00:03:41,130 --> 00:03:42,750
Moron...

24
00:03:41,530 --> 00:03:44,410
Usopp! Stay with me!

25
00:03:45,870 --> 00:03:47,160
– Usopp!
– Usopp!

26
00:03:47,530 --> 00:03:50,330
Clouds... What?!

27
00:03:50,330 --> 00:03:51,790
These are clouds, aren't they?!

28
00:03:51,790 --> 00:03:54,290
But there are so many!
What is all this?!

29
00:03:54,290 --> 00:03:58,100
Basically, this is
an ocean... in the sky?

30
00:03:58,100 --> 00:04:00,090
An ocean in the sky?!

31
00:04:01,550 --> 00:04:04,650
But look! The log pose
is still pointing upward!

32
00:04:04,650 --> 00:04:07,650
We must be midway through
the cumuloimperator clouds.

33
00:04:07,650 --> 00:04:10,070
We need to go even higher? How?

34
00:04:10,070 --> 00:04:11,930
That, I don't know...

35
00:04:11,930 --> 00:04:13,660
Did you call me a moron?!

36
00:04:13,660 --> 00:04:15,000
I forget.

37
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:16,770
An ocean...!

38
00:04:18,410 --> 00:04:22,240
In swimming lane number one,
Captain Usopp!

39
00:04:22,240 --> 00:04:23,160
Yay!

40
00:04:23,160 --> 00:04:24,550
You can do it! Good luck!

41
00:04:24,550 --> 00:04:28,490
Hey, now! Don't be reckless!
This ocean's still a mystery!

42
00:04:28,490 --> 00:04:31,250
An ocean's an ocean!

43
00:04:39,030 --> 00:04:44,550
There's so little resistance,
but I can barely see a thing...

44
00:04:44,550 --> 00:04:50,560
Oh! I'm going deeper
and deeper! So easily...!

45
00:04:56,150 --> 00:04:57,320
Hey.

46
00:04:57,860 --> 00:05:00,650
He's... not coming back up.

47
00:05:01,480 --> 00:05:06,210
I was just wondering...
whether this ocean has a bottom.

48
00:05:06,210 --> 00:05:06,910
– You don't mean...!
– You don't mean...!

49
00:05:06,910 --> 00:05:09,240
Did that bastard fall from the clouds?!

50
00:05:09,370 --> 00:05:11,700
Usopp!

51
00:05:11,700 --> 00:05:13,620
I tried warning that moron!

52
00:05:14,010 --> 00:05:15,720
Stretch your arm as far as you can!

53
00:05:15,720 --> 00:05:17,550
But I can't see down there, so-

54
00:05:17,550 --> 00:05:18,790
You can leave it to me!

55
00:05:19,270 --> 00:05:21,800
Ojos Fleurs!

56
00:05:38,540 --> 00:05:39,140
There he is!

57
00:05:39,140 --> 00:05:41,070
Huh?! Where?!

58
00:05:43,530 --> 00:05:45,490
Veinte Fleurs!

59
00:05:50,850 --> 00:05:52,530
Okay! Pull him up!

60
00:05:52,530 --> 00:05:55,540
You got him?! Okay!

61
00:05:56,910 --> 00:05:58,810
Is he heavy?!

62
00:06:00,010 --> 00:06:01,210
Luffy! You can do it!

63
00:06:01,210 --> 00:06:02,040
You can do it!

64
00:06:04,880 --> 00:06:07,090
Yes! He's back up!

65
00:06:08,090 --> 00:06:10,580
But he's not alone!

66
00:06:10,580 --> 00:06:12,470
They wanna eat Usopp!

67
00:06:15,390 --> 00:06:17,600
It's nothing to be that afraid of!

68
00:06:21,650 --> 00:06:22,650
Huh?!

69
00:06:43,880 --> 00:06:47,900
Y'know... it sure is hard...
to breathe up here...

70
00:06:47,900 --> 00:06:53,390
This is one strange creature...
I'm not even sure if it's a fish.

71
00:06:53,390 --> 00:06:55,960
That octopus was like a balloon!

72
00:06:55,960 --> 00:06:58,270
It's definitely an animal.
It was moving.

73
00:06:58,270 --> 00:07:00,320
Clouds supporting life...?

74
00:07:00,320 --> 00:07:03,860
Perhaps we should think of
these clouds as an ocean.

75
00:07:03,860 --> 00:07:06,440
What's this flat snake?

76
00:07:06,440 --> 00:07:08,260
A flounder! Because it's flat!

77
00:07:08,260 --> 00:07:10,070
So this is a flounder?!

78
00:07:15,650 --> 00:07:18,230
Dammit! What is it this time, Usopp?!

79
00:07:18,230 --> 00:07:20,650
My pants! There was
something in them!

80
00:07:20,650 --> 00:07:22,460
Usopp!

81
00:07:22,460 --> 00:07:25,650
Sky island scary, sky island scary...

82
00:07:25,650 --> 00:07:27,240
It's really not your day.

83
00:07:29,970 --> 00:07:32,720
Isn't this... a sky fish?

84
00:07:32,720 --> 00:07:35,600
These odd fish were
described in Noland's logbook.

85
00:07:35,610 --> 00:07:42,560
They must have evolved to survive
in this bottomless sky ocean.

86
00:07:42,870 --> 00:07:45,960
So they turned all balloon-like
and flat and stuff?

87
00:07:45,960 --> 00:07:48,370
They needed to become lighter...

88
00:07:48,370 --> 00:07:51,590
because the buoyancy here is
weaker than in the oceans below.

89
00:07:51,590 --> 00:07:55,280
They have scales like feathers
and weird, carnivorous mouths!

90
00:07:56,620 --> 00:07:58,260
I tried sautéing it.

91
00:07:58,260 --> 00:07:59,420
This is good!

92
00:07:59,420 --> 00:08:01,290
We were still inspecting it!

93
00:08:01,290 --> 00:08:03,110
What were you guys thinking?!

94
00:08:03,110 --> 00:08:04,720
Oh! It really is good!

95
00:08:04,720 --> 00:08:07,090
What is this?! I've never
had anything like it!

96
00:08:07,090 --> 00:08:09,060
Is it to your liking, Nami?

97
00:08:09,060 --> 00:08:10,800
Let's eat the big one next!

98
00:08:11,110 --> 00:08:13,110
Where is the sky island?

99
00:08:13,110 --> 00:08:14,380
Oh! A ship...

100
00:08:14,860 --> 00:08:18,850
A ship! Hey, guys!
A ship... and a person?

101
00:08:18,850 --> 00:08:20,040
Huh?

102
00:08:20,720 --> 00:08:22,520
What?!

103
00:08:22,520 --> 00:08:25,030
Hey. What's wrong, Chopper?

104
00:08:26,900 --> 00:08:29,090
Is there a ship out there, Chopper?

105
00:08:29,090 --> 00:08:32,030
No, uh, there was,
but not anymore...!

106
00:08:32,030 --> 00:08:33,430
Huh?

107
00:08:33,430 --> 00:08:35,280
A bull—with a square head?—

108
00:08:35,280 --> 00:08:37,740
is running on the clouds!

109
00:08:35,970 --> 00:08:37,740
You're not making sense! Calm down!

110
00:08:37,740 --> 00:08:40,200
What's wrong with you...? Huh?!

111
00:08:41,790 --> 00:08:43,960
It's a person! Someone's coming!

112
00:08:43,960 --> 00:08:45,790
He's running on the clouds!

113
00:08:47,330 --> 00:08:49,090
Hey, stop! What do you want?!

114
00:08:49,090 --> 00:08:50,170
Your deaths!

115
00:08:50,170 --> 00:08:51,810
Looks like he wants to fight!

116
00:08:51,810 --> 00:08:52,670
Fine by me!

117
00:08:52,670 --> 00:08:53,720
What's going on?!

118
00:09:01,520 --> 00:09:04,100
H-Hey! What's with you three?!

119
00:09:10,900 --> 00:09:12,070
He's gonna shoot us!

120
00:09:12,070 --> 00:09:14,320
Sky island scary, sky island scary...

121
00:09:15,300 --> 00:09:16,780
Stop right there!

122
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:32,170
What?! Another weirdo?!

123
00:09:39,380 --> 00:09:42,780
I am the Sky Knight.

124
00:09:49,380 --> 00:09:51,220
He's gone...

125
00:09:51,780 --> 00:09:55,540
What the heck's going on?!
Who was that?!

126
00:09:55,540 --> 00:10:00,990
And what's with you guys?!
You're pathetic, losing three against one!

127
00:10:00,990 --> 00:10:03,090
Thank you for saving us!

128
00:10:03,090 --> 00:10:06,160
It was unavoidable.
This one is on the house.

129
00:10:06,710 --> 00:10:10,040
Man... Talk about being worthless...

130
00:10:10,040 --> 00:10:14,300
It's hard to move... for some reason...

131
00:10:14,300 --> 00:10:17,110
It must be because of the thin air.

132
00:10:17,110 --> 00:10:19,970
Yeah, now that you mention it...

133
00:10:19,970 --> 00:10:21,670
Are you Blue Sea people?

134
00:10:21,670 --> 00:10:25,180
What do you mean by
"Blue Sea people"? Also, who are you?

135
00:10:25,180 --> 00:10:27,220
I am the Sky Knight.

136
00:10:27,220 --> 00:10:30,610
"Blue Sea people" are those
who live beneath the clouds.

137
00:10:30,610 --> 00:10:33,610
I take it you come up here
from the blue sea?

138
00:10:33,610 --> 00:10:34,870
Yeah! That's right!

139
00:10:34,870 --> 00:10:36,240
Then that explains it.

140
00:10:36,240 --> 00:10:39,990
This is the White Sea,
7,000 meters up.

141
00:10:39,990 --> 00:10:44,530
Higher still is the White-White Sea
at an elevation of 10,000 meters.

142
00:10:44,530 --> 00:10:47,410
Ordinary Blue Sea people
can't possibly endure it here.

143
00:10:47,410 --> 00:10:49,550
Alright! I've gotten used to it!

144
00:10:49,550 --> 00:10:52,040
Yeah. I feel much better now.

145
00:10:52,040 --> 00:10:54,520
No, no, no! That is not possible!

146
00:10:54,520 --> 00:10:58,170
Anyway, how was that guy
running on top of the clouds?!

147
00:10:58,500 --> 00:11:00,020
Now, now. Hold on.

148
00:11:00,020 --> 00:11:04,410
I'm sure you have many questions,
but let's talk business first.

149
00:11:04,410 --> 00:11:05,830
Business?

150
00:11:05,830 --> 00:11:09,990
I am a freelance soldier-for-hire.
These seas are fraught with danger.

151
00:11:09,990 --> 00:11:11,980
If you don't know how
to fight in the sky,

152
00:11:11,980 --> 00:11:16,320
guerrillas like that one will come after you
and turn you into sky fish food.

153
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:20,490
For five million extol per whistle,
I will come to your aid.

154
00:11:22,840 --> 00:11:24,620
What nonsense is that, old guy?

155
00:11:24,620 --> 00:11:29,450
What?! That is quite cheap!
I won't lower it a single extol more!

156
00:11:29,450 --> 00:11:31,520
I need to earn a living too, you know!

157
00:11:31,520 --> 00:11:36,090
What in the world is "extol"?
And what's this "whistle" or whatever?

158
00:11:36,090 --> 00:11:40,760
You came here via the summit
of High West, did you not?

159
00:11:40,760 --> 00:11:43,180
Then you must have
passed an island or two.

160
00:11:43,180 --> 00:11:45,530
Again, what kinda
nonsense is that, old guy?

161
00:11:45,530 --> 00:11:49,510
Wait! You mean there are other ways
of coming to this sky ocean?!

162
00:11:49,510 --> 00:11:53,230
And "an island or two"? Does that
mean there are lots of sky islands?!

163
00:11:53,650 --> 00:11:55,770
Don't tell me you came here via the...

164
00:11:55,770 --> 00:11:58,070
We rode the Knock-Up Stream.

165
00:11:58,070 --> 00:12:01,030
My word! That monstrous current?!

166
00:12:01,030 --> 00:12:04,320
So there are still people
gutsy enough for that...

167
00:12:04,320 --> 00:12:08,240
It wasn't the normal route, after all...!

168
00:12:08,240 --> 00:12:10,020
We could've died, you know!

169
00:12:10,020 --> 00:12:13,000
We could've done it safely
if we'd gathered more intel!

170
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:15,030
What's it matter now?
We're already here.

171
00:12:15,030 --> 00:12:17,710
Sky island scary, sky island scary...

172
00:12:18,200 --> 00:12:19,710
Did you lose any of your crew?

173
00:12:20,180 --> 00:12:21,550
No, we're all here.

174
00:12:21,550 --> 00:12:24,170
That would not have been so
with any other route.

175
00:12:24,170 --> 00:12:25,800
When you head into the sky,

176
00:12:25,800 --> 00:12:30,580
there's no telling how many of your
comrades will survive the journey.

177
00:12:30,580 --> 00:12:34,920
But with the Knock-Up Stream,
everyone dies or everyone arrives.

178
00:12:34,920 --> 00:12:36,020
That's it.

179
00:12:36,020 --> 00:12:39,580
Not many can make
that all-or-nothing bet,

180
00:12:39,580 --> 00:12:41,130
especially these days.

181
00:12:41,130 --> 00:12:45,990
Now I see that you are capable
navigators with courage and skill.

182
00:12:47,030 --> 00:12:50,170
Yes, I must admit,
it was only because I was here!

183
00:12:50,170 --> 00:12:53,430
These guys were on their knees
crying and giving up on life,

184
00:12:53,430 --> 00:12:57,210
and I told them, "I will navigate us–"

185
00:12:56,720 --> 00:12:57,210
Hold on!

186
00:12:57,210 --> 00:13:01,420
With one whistle—
I mean one blow of this whistle—

187
00:13:03,010 --> 00:13:07,340
I shall descend from the heavens
and come to your aid!

188
00:13:07,340 --> 00:13:10,550
Normally, I would charge
five million extol,

189
00:13:10,550 --> 00:13:13,350
but I will give you
one whistle as a present!

190
00:13:13,350 --> 00:13:15,230
Wait! We still don't know your name!

191
00:13:16,580 --> 00:13:21,880
I am Gan Fall, the Sky Knight!
And this is my partner, Pierre!

192
00:13:23,150 --> 00:13:26,280
I forgot to mention it,
but my partner, Pierre...

193
00:13:29,830 --> 00:13:33,330
is a bird that ate the Horse-Horse Fruit
and gained its powers.

194
00:13:36,040 --> 00:13:36,710
The bird's...?!

195
00:13:36,710 --> 00:13:39,670
In short, he becomes
a horse with wings!

196
00:13:39,670 --> 00:13:41,380
Namely...

197
00:13:41,380 --> 00:13:43,880
No way! Wow! A Pegasus?!

198
00:13:43,880 --> 00:13:45,940
Yes! A Pegasus!

199
00:13:49,140 --> 00:13:51,810
– How... disappointing.
– How... disappointing.

200
00:13:51,810 --> 00:13:55,140
May luck be with you, heroes!

201
00:13:56,980 --> 00:13:59,520
That was a weird thing it turned into...

202
00:13:59,520 --> 00:14:02,460
In the end, he didn't tell us anything.

203
00:14:02,460 --> 00:14:05,010
You're right! Nothing at all!

204
00:14:05,010 --> 00:14:07,070
Now we're back to square one.

205
00:14:07,570 --> 00:14:09,540
How do we get up there?!

206
00:14:09,540 --> 00:14:13,100
I know! Let's call
that old guy and ask!

207
00:14:13,100 --> 00:14:15,340
H-H-Hold on, Luffy!

208
00:14:15,340 --> 00:14:18,450
This is only supposed to be
used in emergencies!

209
00:14:18,450 --> 00:14:22,980
What if that weird masked
guy shows up again?!

210
00:14:23,690 --> 00:14:26,310
Let's just start sailing somewhere.

211
00:14:26,310 --> 00:14:28,380
Hey, look over there!

212
00:14:28,920 --> 00:14:29,990
What could that be?

213
00:14:29,990 --> 00:14:31,460
What a weird cloud.

214
00:14:31,460 --> 00:14:33,560
It resembles a waterfall...

215
00:14:34,120 --> 00:14:37,320
Alright! It's decided! Let's check it out!

216
00:14:52,840 --> 00:14:54,950
Wait! Stop! Stop!

217
00:14:54,950 --> 00:14:56,920
There are huge clouds in the way...

218
00:14:56,920 --> 00:14:58,710
What do we do?

219
00:14:58,710 --> 00:15:02,690
They're floating on the sky ocean,
so they can't be part of it.

220
00:15:02,690 --> 00:15:04,090
Then what are they?

221
00:15:04,090 --> 00:15:06,420
Ordinary clouds don't stay still.

222
00:15:06,420 --> 00:15:08,050
Let's touch one and find out!

223
00:15:08,490 --> 00:15:12,390
Gum-Gum Pistol!

224
00:15:13,070 --> 00:15:14,010
It bounced off!

225
00:15:19,230 --> 00:15:24,230
Look! I'm on it! I'm not sinking!
It's all fluffy, like cotton!

226
00:15:24,230 --> 00:15:28,150
What is this?!
What is this?! It's too fun!

227
00:15:28,740 --> 00:15:29,830
Wow!

228
00:15:29,830 --> 00:15:31,180
Now how does that work?!

229
00:15:31,180 --> 00:15:32,210
How mysterious...

230
00:15:32,210 --> 00:15:34,410
Me too! I'm coming too!

231
00:15:34,410 --> 00:15:35,740
Me too!

232
00:15:38,200 --> 00:15:39,660
This feels great!

233
00:15:39,660 --> 00:15:42,080
It's warm and makes me
wanna sleep right here!

234
00:15:42,080 --> 00:15:44,710
It's even better than
a freshly-aired futon!

235
00:15:51,170 --> 00:15:57,010
But this means the ship can't go
through places filled with these...

236
00:15:57,010 --> 00:16:00,180
Hey! Find a route the ship can take
while you're up there!

237
00:16:01,180 --> 00:16:02,380
Right! Okay!

238
00:16:02,380 --> 00:16:05,230
Hey, Luffy! There's
something over here!

239
00:16:05,230 --> 00:16:05,830
What is it?!

240
00:16:05,830 --> 00:16:08,320
Hey! Where are you going?!
Quit playing around!

241
00:16:12,280 --> 00:16:13,250
What is that?

242
00:16:13,250 --> 00:16:14,360
A gate?

243
00:16:14,360 --> 00:16:18,410
Yeah! There's a big gate
under that waterfall thingy!

244
00:16:20,120 --> 00:16:23,030
There are man-made objects
in a place like this?

245
00:16:23,030 --> 00:16:27,000
At this point, nothing in this
ocean would surprise me.

246
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:28,930
We'll know once we get through here!

247
00:16:28,930 --> 00:16:30,110
Left next!

248
00:16:30,110 --> 00:16:31,180
No, right!

249
00:16:31,180 --> 00:16:32,650
It's to our left!

250
00:16:32,650 --> 00:16:34,080
No, our right!

251
00:16:34,080 --> 00:16:35,720
Let's call the old armor guy!

252
00:16:35,720 --> 00:16:36,980
Stop that!

253
00:16:38,520 --> 00:16:40,180
Alright! Looks like we made it!

254
00:16:47,450 --> 00:16:49,060
It's a gate, all right...

255
00:16:49,060 --> 00:16:52,820
And look, that waterfall-like cloud
really was a waterfall!

256
00:16:52,820 --> 00:16:55,910
It's flowing over those same
weird clouds from earlier!

257
00:16:55,910 --> 00:17:00,040
Let's see. It says, "Heaven's Gate"...
That's kind of ominous!

258
00:17:00,040 --> 00:17:02,870
It sounds like we're on our way to die!

259
00:17:02,870 --> 00:17:06,850
Y'know, maybe we're already dead.

260
00:17:06,850 --> 00:17:10,640
Ah! That would explain
this weird world...

261
00:17:10,640 --> 00:17:13,310
Ack! We're dead?!

262
00:17:13,310 --> 00:17:15,590
Heaven, huh? This is gonna be great!

263
00:17:15,590 --> 00:17:17,590
I finally get to go there!

264
00:17:17,590 --> 00:17:19,160
Get real!

265
00:17:19,160 --> 00:17:20,260
What was that for?!

266
00:17:20,260 --> 00:17:22,230
Your jokes aren't funny!

267
00:17:22,230 --> 00:17:24,550
Why did I get hit, too...?

268
00:17:25,230 --> 00:17:28,570
Look! Over there!
Someone's coming out!

269
00:17:36,150 --> 00:17:37,160
It's an angel!

270
00:17:37,160 --> 00:17:40,200
Is that what angels are like?!
She looks like a raisin!

271
00:17:41,160 --> 00:17:44,580
Sightseeing? Or perhaps... war?

272
00:17:46,040 --> 00:17:48,040
It doesn't matter either way.

273
00:17:48,040 --> 00:17:49,830
If you're going to the upper area,

274
00:17:49,830 --> 00:17:53,420
pay the entrance fee
of one billion extol per person.

275
00:17:53,420 --> 00:17:54,790
That is the law.

276
00:17:54,790 --> 00:17:56,670
O-One billion?!

277
00:17:56,670 --> 00:17:59,000
There's that "extol" stuff again...

278
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:02,510
How much is a billion extol in belly?

279
00:18:02,510 --> 00:18:07,450
Whatever it is, one billion
sounds really expensive!

280
00:18:07,450 --> 00:18:11,190
One billion per person...
Seven billion for seven people...

281
00:18:11,190 --> 00:18:12,970
It's just to enter the country!

282
00:18:12,970 --> 00:18:16,150
Do countries usually charge
that much just to enter?!

283
00:18:16,150 --> 00:18:17,740
This old lady's trying to scam–

284
00:18:17,740 --> 00:18:23,160
Um, about the money...
What if... What if we can't pay?

285
00:18:23,160 --> 00:18:24,620
You may pass.

286
00:18:24,620 --> 00:18:25,870
Are you serious?!

287
00:18:25,870 --> 00:18:29,660
Or you may not pass.

288
00:18:30,960 --> 00:18:36,800
I am neither a gatekeeper nor a guard.
I simply ask your intentions.

289
00:18:36,800 --> 00:18:39,330
Then let's go! To the sky island!

290
00:18:39,330 --> 00:18:41,560
We can't pay, but we're
going through anyway!

291
00:18:41,560 --> 00:18:44,560
I see. The seven of you, then?

292
00:18:45,560 --> 00:18:49,020
Yeah. But how do we
get to the sky island–

293
00:18:54,170 --> 00:18:56,480
What the...?! Something's here!

294
00:18:56,930 --> 00:19:00,570
The White Sea's
famous express lobster...

295
00:19:02,950 --> 00:19:04,830
It's moving!

296
00:19:04,830 --> 00:19:06,440
It's a huge lobster!

297
00:19:06,440 --> 00:19:08,120
Is it going up the waterfall?!

298
00:19:08,550 --> 00:19:09,680
Hold on tight!

299
00:19:09,680 --> 00:19:11,720
What speed!

300
00:19:16,130 --> 00:19:18,700
It's still a ways to the top!

301
00:19:23,720 --> 00:19:28,310
This is Inspector Amazon
of Heaven's Gate!

302
00:19:28,310 --> 00:19:32,500
Attention, almighty God
and his priests...

303
00:19:32,500 --> 00:19:36,710
Seven illegal entrants are heading
into God Land Skypiea...

304
00:19:36,710 --> 00:19:39,650
May they receive Divine Reckoning!

305
00:19:47,080 --> 00:19:51,320
May they receive Divine Reckoning!

306
00:17:32,030 --> 00:17:36,150
Inspector Amazon
Heaven's Gate

307
00:17:32,030 --> 00:17:36,150
Inspector Amazon
Heaven's Gate

